  "description": "**Porto Metropolitan Area (AMP)** — 17 municipalities, 1.7M inhabitants.\n\n(Vibecoded with Claude )\n\n## Demand Model\n- 59,992 O/D pairs generated from **INE BGRI 2021** (census tract level)\n- **1.20M simulated passengers** — 70.6% population coverage\n- Realistic urban drive-times (20/30/60 km/h by zone + 20% congestion penalty)\n- Captive boost for low car-ownership areas (Porto ×1.8, Gaia ×1.6, Matosinhos ×1.35)\n\n## Points of Interest\n- Francisco Sá Carneiro Airport, Port of Leixões, Cruise Terminal\n- Major hospitals (São João, Santo António, Pedro Hispano) and universities (UP, FEUP, ISEP)\n- CP rail stations (Campanhã, São Bento, Devesas) and bus terminals\n- 30+ tourist POIs: Ribeira, Torre dos Clérigos, Serralves, Casa da Música, Port Wine Caves\n\n## Coverage\n- Full detail up to zoom 15 across the AMP\n- Northern Portugal at low zoom (Braga, Aveiro, Viana do Castelo, Bragança) for geographic context",
